<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="180" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,756,673,1019]" pageId="8" pageNumber="180">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,264,673,697]" pageId="8" pageNumber="180">Remarks:</emphasis>
The species is in external characters similar with 
<taxonomicName authority="Lobl, 1997" authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="1997" box="[209,474,705,729]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="commune">
<emphasis box="[209,343,707,729]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="180">S. commune</emphasis>
Löbl, 1997
</taxonomicName>
[a replacement name for the homonymous 
<taxonomicName authority="(Motschulsky, 1845)" baseAuthorityName="Motschulsky" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[354,745,737,761]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castaneum">
<emphasis box="[354,501,739,761]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="180">S. castaneum</emphasis>
(Motschulsky, 1845)
</taxonomicName>
]. The puncture pattern of the metaventrite and ventrite I enables reliable identification. In addition, the aedeagi of these species differ drastically: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="1997" box="[517,646,836,858]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="commune">
<emphasis box="[517,646,836,858]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="180">S. commune</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses a long, thin flagellum extruded in repose while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1825" box="[151,288,900,922]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convexum">
<emphasis box="[151,288,900,922]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="180">S. convexum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a robust rod as illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation author="Leschen R. A. B. &amp; Lobl I. &amp; Stephen K." pageId="8" pageNumber="180" pagination="274 - 294" refId="ref9941" refString="Leschen R. A. B., Lobl I., Stephen K. 1990. Review of the Ozark Highland Scaphisoma (Coleoptera: Scaphidiidae). The Coleopterists Bulletin 44: 274 - 294." type="journal article" year="1990">
Leschen 
<emphasis box="[151,210,932,954]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="180">et al.</emphasis>
(1990)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1825" box="[312,561,932,954]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convexum">
<emphasis box="[312,561,932,954]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="180">Scaphisoma convexum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be collected in numbers from basidiomycete fungi (
<bibRefCitation author="Newton A. F. Jr." box="[591,752,962,986]" pageId="8" pageNumber="180" pagination="302 - 353" refId="ref10152" refString="Newton A. F. Jr. 1984. Mycophagy in Staphylinoidea (Coleopetra) (pp. 302 - 353). In: Wheeler Q., Blackwell M. (eds). Fungus / insect relationships. Perspectives in ecology and evolution. Columbia University Press, New York, 514 pp." type="book chapter" year="1984">Newton, 1984</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Leschen R. A. B. &amp; Lobl I. &amp; Stephen K." box="[151,371,994,1019]" pageId="8" pageNumber="180" pagination="274 - 294" refId="ref9941" refString="Leschen R. A. B., Lobl I., Stephen K. 1990. Review of the Ozark Highland Scaphisoma (Coleoptera: Scaphidiidae). The Coleopterists Bulletin 44: 274 - 294." type="journal article" year="1990">
Leschen 
<emphasis box="[247,307,997,1019]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="180">et al.,</emphasis>
1990
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
